The paper deals with communication and networking in vehicular ad-hoc networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses issues related to security and reliability, which could place it under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Fog computing is a key component of the proposed approach, which could place it under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also deals with the adaptation of the algorithm to changes in the environment, which could place it under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the simulation aspect of the paper could place it under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
